\subtree{
\title{Troubleshooting}
\subtree{
\title{Common Issues}
\p{\strong{Problem}: Report is under 50 pages}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Solution}: Expand data tables in appendices, add more detailed company profiles, include additional regional breakdowns}
}

\p{\strong{Problem}: Visuals not rendering}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Solution}: Check file paths in LaTeX, ensure images are in figures/ folder, verify file extensions}
}

\p{\strong{Problem}: Bibliography missing entries}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Solution}: Run bibtex after first xelatex pass, check .bib file for syntax errors}
}

\p{\strong{Problem}: Table/figure overflow}

\ul{
\li{\startverb **Solution**: Use `\resizebox` or `adjustbox` package, reduce image width percentage\stopverb}
}

\p{\strong{Problem}: Poor visual quality from generation}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Solution}: Use \code{\startverb --doc-type report\stopverb} flag, increase iterations with \code{\startverb --iterations 5\stopverb}}
}

\p{Use this skill to create comprehensive, visually-rich market research reports that rival top consulting firm deliverables. The combination of deep research, structured frameworks, and extensive visualization produces documents that inform strategic decisions and demonstrate analytical rigor.}
}
}
}